function robo_admin_page() {
?>
<div class="wrap"><h2><b><a href="http://wp-thumbnail.robocasters.com" target="_blank">WP-Thumbnail</a> by <a href="http://robocasters.com" target="_blank">Robocasters</a></b></h2><p style="font-size: 14px">WP-Thumbnail is a simple and neat Wordpress Plugin that not only allows you to use a short-code to generate dynamic screenshot of webpages in your posts but also takes a realtime snapshot of the served webpage and saves a link to it on the page itself that too without burdening the servers. This helps in optimizing search results on Google by adding a thumbnail to the left of the search result snippet and makes shared posts more attractive, with a relevant thumbnails, on Social Sites like Facebook.</p><table style="width: 100%;border-top: dashed 1px;padding-top: 15px"><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;"><table class="widefat form-table"><tbody><tr><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>Features</strong></th><td style="border: 1px solid;">Lets explore the features of WP-Thumbnail and know what it is capable of.</td></tr><tr class="alternate"><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>Short-Code</strong><div style="font-size: 10px;color: gray;">The plugin has a shortcode that enables you to add dynamic screenshots of webpages to your post.</div></th><td style="border: 1px solid;"><b>[roboshot url="WEB ADDRESS" width="IN PX" newpage="TRUE/FALSE" link="TRUE/FALSE" refresh="TRUE/FALSE"]</b><br/><br/><b>url</b>- It contains the url of webpage. (Plain text not Hyperlink. Must have 'http://'.)<br/><b>width</b>- Width of Screenshot in Pixels.<br/><b>newpage</b>- Whether or not you want to open link in new page. (optional, default: true)<br/><b>link</b>- If you want to give link to the image.(optional, default: true)<br/><b>refresh</b>- If you want to reload the screenshot, if it wasn't generated on the first call. (optional, default: true)<br/></td></tr><tr class=""><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>Meta Thumbnail</strong><div style="font-size: 10px;color: gray;">It uses meta name thumbnail and adds the live screenshot in it for being displayed as a thumbnail in Google Searches.</div></th><td style="border: 1px solid;">This helps Google to recognize the image as thumbnail for the search result.<br/><br/><b><meta name="thumbnail" content="IMG SRC"/></b></td></tr><tr class="alternate"><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>PageMaps</strong><div style="font-size: 10px;color: gray;">PageMaps is a structured data format that provides Google with information about the data on a page. It enables website creators to embed data and notes in webpages.</div></th><td style="border: 1px solid;">We use PageMaps to tell Google about the image for the same purpose but in more specified way telling its width and height. This leaves no chance for Google to show snippet without thumbnail.<br/></br><b><PageMap><DataObject type="thumbnail"><Attribute name="src" value="IMG SRC"/><Attribute name="width" value="200"/><Attribute name="height" value="150"/></DataObject></PageMap></b></td></tr><tr class=""><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>Facebook OG:Image</strong><div style="font-size: 10px;color: gray;">It sets image with content og:image to the top priority for being used as a Facebook Post thumbnail.</div></th><td style="border: 1px solid;">The Facebook scripts are a bit loose they may sometime time-out without grabbing all the images and leaving the relevant ones. This tag makes sure that how loose the script may be it will never leave this image and add a relevant thumbnail.<br/><br/><b><meta property="og:image" content="IMG SRC"/></b></td></tr><tr class="alternate"><th style="vertical-align: top;border: 1px solid;"><strong>WP-Thumbnail Class</strong><div style="font-size: 10px;color: gray;">It adds a WP-Thumbnail class that helps image to be used for all other sharing purposes.</div></th><td style="border: 1px solid;">It adds simple lines of HTML codes to the page without changing the design of your page but allowing you share the thumbnails on all other sites but don't have scripts running for the recognition of image in meta contents.</td></tr></tbody></table></td><td style="width: 200px;vertical-align: top;padding-top: 8px;" align="center"><div class="postbox" align="center" style="margin-left: 5px;width: 310px"><h3 class="hndle" align="left" style="padding: 3px 2px 3px 3px"><span>About the Plugin :</span></h3><div class="inside"><table class="form-table side"><tr><td style="font-size: 11px;background: white;"><a href="http://wp-thumbnail.robocasters.com" target="_blank">Plugin Homepage</a><br/>Know more about the plugin and its upadated versions at the official website of WP-Thumbnail.</td></tr><tr class="alt"><td style="font-size: 11px;background: #E0E0E0"><a href="http://robocasters.com" target="_blank">Author's Website</a><br/>Like the plugin? Know more about its author - Robocasters. Read his blog, visit the portfolio or contact him.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size: 11px;background: white;"><a href="http://robocasters.com/#text-5" target="_blank">Get Notified - Subscribe</a><br/>Are curious about the next plugin or just simply want updates about this plugin even before Wordpress, go and subscribe.</td></tr><tr class="alt"><td style="font-size: 11px;background: #E0E0E0"><a href="http://robocasters.com/forums/forum/site-commentscomplaintssuggestions/wp-thumbnail/" target="_blank">Plugin Discussion Forum</a><br/>Have some cool ideas that you think can be added to this plugin or just want to know whats coming next, join the discussion forums.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size: 11px;background: white;"><a href="http://robocasters.com/forums/forum/site-commentscomplaintssuggestions/wp-thumbnail/" target="_blank">Report a Bug</a><br/>Getting a problem, don't worry just report a bug in the forums section with tag - 'bug' and the rest is my part.</td></tr></table></div></div><div class="postbox" align="center" style="margin-left: 5px;width: 310px;height: 115px;margin-top: -15px;"><h3 class="hndle" align="left" style="padding: 3px 2px 3px 3px"><span>Help me build more :</span></h3><div class="inside"><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[ */ (function(){var s=document.createElement('script'), t=document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];s.type='text/javascript';s.async=true;s.src='http://api.flattr.com/js/0.6/load.js?mode=auto';t.parentNode.insertBefore(s, t);})();/*]]> */</script><a class="FlattrButton" style="display:none;" href="http://wp-thumbnail.robocasters.com"></a><noscript><a href="http://flattr.com/thing/932050/WP-Thumbnail" target="_blank"><img src="http://api.flattr.com/button/flattr-badge-large.png" alt="Flattr this" title="Flattr this" border="0"/></a></noscript></div></div></td></tr></table></div>
